    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e875c3df_93e8ec8d",
        "filename": "infra_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 91,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-28T14:57:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We can do this:\n\ns.Step().Env(env).Do(func(s *Step)error {\n    // Here are all of the steps that need env.\n})\n\nThe \"downside\" is that you\u0027d get an intermediate umbrella step which has those as sub-steps.  IMO it\u0027s reasonable to organize steps with common properties that way.  Also, a Step inherits the environment of its parent.  So, we could do this higher up and then not need to re-specify it.",
      "parentUuid": "815da7a6_e3447d14",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 91,
        "startChar": 46,
        "endLine": 91,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "623adc3efbde9e3daece6e8fc1b01d1742375182",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c8c07e7b_80ae9821",
        "filename": "infra_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 91,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-28T14:57:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s calling into exec.RunCwd, which is why it\u0027s named that way.  Interpret it as \"Run this command in the given current working directory\"",
      "parentUuid": "81841911_d721361a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 91,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 91,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "623adc3efbde9e3daece6e8fc1b01d1742375182",
